<TITLE> Govt extends deadline for firearms deposit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, December 2 (bdnews24.com)The home ministry on Tuesday extended the deadline for depositing licensed firearms and ammunition to Dec 14, ahead of the forthcoming Jatiya Sangsad and Upazila elections. A ministry order signed by deputy secretary Ghiasuddin Ahmed said carrying of any firearm or ammunition is prohibited during the upcoming election period. Bearing firearms has been prohibited from Dec 15 to Jan 31. Licensed guns and ammunition may be deposited with local police stations on or before Dec 14. The concerned authorities have been asked to submit an account of the arms deposited with police stations, to the office of the inspector general of police, by Dec 18. The Jatiya Sangsad election is scheduled for Dec 29, Upazila polls for Jan 22. bd
